text: The Sehol A5 is a Compact car produced by JAC Motors under the Sehol sub- brand. It was first introduced in 2019 and The car is available in both petrol and electric versions. == History == The Sehol A5 was launched in 2019, as a successor to the JAC J5. It was initially called the JAC Jiayue A5 until 2021, when the name was changed to Sehol A5. The car is built in Hefei, China, and has been in production since its release. == Markets == The Sehol A5 is sold primarily in China and has been made available in other regions, including Kazakhstan, Mexico, Russia, and in the Middle East, where it is sold as the JAC J7. == References == Category:Chinese automobiles
